<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFFB0147600EF1F397B588A8" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFFB0147600EF1F397B588A8" blockId="25.[828,1437,499,906]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB0147600EF1F390CE8928" bold="true" box="[828,959,499,522]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB014760F8F1F397FC8928" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1895" box="[970,1165,499,522]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balyi">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB014760F8F1F397FC8928" box="[970,1165,499,522]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Platyxantha balyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species completely overlooked by all subsequent authors and thus missing in all catalogues and publications. It was described from 
<collectingRegion id="462391AAFFFB0147600EF25390088948" box="[828,889,595,618]" country="Malaysia" name="Perak" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Perak</collectingRegion>
from an unspecified number of specimens, however, Jacoby must have had at least two specimens as he mentioned length span. In the BMNH I have found two 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFFB0147600EF2B390E989E8" box="[828,920,691,714]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">syntypes</typeStatus>
(females) belonging to two different species. One female is certainly 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB01476734F2D3970A89C8" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1865" box="[1030,1147,723,746]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hyphaenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB01476734F2D3970A89C8" box="[1030,1147,723,746]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Hyphaenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is designated here as a 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFFB0147600EF2F390EF8828" box="[828,926,755,778]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="1CDC43CDFFFB0147609EF2F3977A8828" box="[940,1035,755,778]" captionStart="Figs 105–112" captionStartId="24.[151,188,1945,1964]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,333,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[180,1408,333,1921]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 105–112. Habitus of species excluded from Taumacera. 105 – Fleutiauxia chinensis (Maulik, 1933) (male, syntype); 106 – F. chinensis (female, syntype of F. mutifrons Gressitt &amp; Kimoto, 1963); 107 – Hoplosaenidea abdominalis (Jacoby, 1884) (male, holotype of Platyxantha wallacei Jacoby, 1895); 108 – Hoplosaenidea dohertyi (Jacoby, 1894) (female, syntype); 109 – Hyphaenia balyi (Jacoby, 1895) (female, lectotype); 110 – Pseudoscelida nigrolimbata (Jacoby, 1899) (male, syntype); 111 – Metrioidea grandis (Allard, 1889) (male, syntype of Platyxantha robusta Jacoby, 1895); 112 – Theopella bodjoensis (Duvivier, 1885) (female, syntype of Platyxantha quadraticollis Jacoby, 1896)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505542/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Fig. 109</figureCitation>
). The other female is a representative of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB0147606AF31390888808" authorityName="Laboissiere" authorityYear="1933" box="[856,1017,787,810]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hoplosaenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB0147606AF31390888808" box="[856,1017,787,810]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Hoplosaenidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but I am unable to assign it to any species at the moment. The 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFFB0147670FF33397EE8868" box="[1085,1183,819,842]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">lectotype</typeStatus>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB01476615F33397278848" authority="Mohamedsaid, 1998" authorityName="Mohamedsaid" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hyphaenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azlani">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB01476615F333900D8848" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Hyphaenia azlani</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFFB014760B3F35397278848" author="MOHAMEDSAID M. S." box="[897,1110,851,874]" firstAuthor="Mohamedsaid" journalOrPublisher="Serangga" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" pagination="67 - 85" part="3" refId="ref32759" refString="MOHAMEDSAID M. S. 1998 a: Checklist of the Galerucinae from Taman Negara Gunung Gading, Sarawak (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Serangga 3: 67 - 85." title="Checklist of the Galerucinae from Taman Negara Gunung Gading, Sarawak (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)" type="journal article" year="1998">Mohamedsaid, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but I avoid synonymizing them without the study of type specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
